## Disclaimer

**⚠️ IMPORTANT DISCLAIMER**

This is Bitcoin wallet software. By using Grimm App, you acknowledge and agree to the following:

- **Self-Custody Responsibility**: You are solely responsible for securing your seed phrase. If you lose your seed phrase, your Bitcoin will be permanently lost. There is no "forgot password" option and no one can help you recover your funds.

- **No Warranty**: This software is provided "as is" without warranty of any kind. While we strive for the highest security and reliability, bugs may exist.

- **User Responsibility**: You are responsible for understanding how Bitcoin works before using this wallet. Transactions are irreversible, and mistakes can result in permanent loss of funds.

- **No Liability**: The developers and contributors are not liable for any losses, damages, or issues arising from the use of this software, including but not limited to loss of Bitcoin, failed transactions, or security breaches.

- **Beta Software**: This is beta software under active development. Use caution and don't store more Bitcoin than you can afford to lose during the beta period.

- **Regulatory Compliance**: You are responsible for complying with all applicable laws and regulations in your jurisdiction regarding the use of Bitcoin and cryptocurrency.

- **Security Best Practices**: Always verify addresses before sending, never share your seed phrase, keep your device secure, and backup your wallet properly.

**By using Grimm App, you accept full responsibility for your funds and actions.**

## Acknowledgements

### Built With

- [Obytes Starter](https://starter.obytes.com) - Production-ready React Native template
- [Breez SDK](https://breez.technology/) - Lightning Network integration
- [Bitcoin Dev Kit (BDK)](https://bitcoindevkit.org/) - Bitcoin wallet functionality (planned)
- [Liquid Wallet Kit (LWK)](https://github.com/Blockstream/lwk) - Liquid Network support (planned)

### Inspired By

- The Bitcoin self-custody movement
- The cypherpunk vision of financial freedom
- Open-source Bitcoin wallet projects: Electrum, Sparrow, Samourai, Zeus

### Special Thanks

- The Bitcoin Core developers
